{
  "texts": [
    "Third, we gathered timings for nonsnapshot aligned queries where the query neurons were edited since the snapshot (median = 1,385 ms, N = 12,303).",
    "By comparing measurements from the first two groups for queries to the same neuron, we can obtain the overhead of the additional logic (median = 447 ms; Fig. 5e).",
    "Although query times were well correlated with query size (Extended Data Fig. 7a), we found this offset to be largely constant across queries (Extended Data Fig.",
    "Queries are slowed down modestly for the third case where the queried segment changed since the last snapshot and an overinclusive query has to be generated (Fig. 5e, f).",
    "We designed CAVE along two broad principles: modularity and openness."
  ]
}